%md 
# Item-Bases Collaborative Filtering
As before, we'll start by importing the MovieLens 100K data set into a pandas DataFrame

msg.data:
Item-Bases Collaborative Filtering

As before, we’ll start by importing the MovieLens 100K data set into a pandas DataFrame

paragraphs.text:
%python
import pandas as pd

r_cols = ['user_id', 'movie_id', 'rating']
ratings = pd.read_csv('/zeppelin/datasets/ml-100k/u.data', sep='\t', names=r_cols, usecols=range(3))
#mr = ratings.pivot_table(index=['user_id'], columns=['movie_id'], values='rating')

m_cols = ['movie_id', 'title']
# Note here we are using u.item2, this is a utf-8 transformed file from the original iso-8859-1 which didn't work well at least on linux and zeppelin
movies = pd.read_csv('/zeppelin/datasets/ml-100k/u.item2', sep='|', names=m_cols, usecols=range(2))

ratings = pd.merge(movies, ratings)

z.show(ratings)

paragraphs.text:
%md

Now, let's go through each movie i rated one at a time, and build up a list of possible recommendations based on the movies similar to the ones i rated.

So for each movie i rated, I'll receive the list of similar movies from our correlation matrix. I'll then scale those correlation scores by how well i rated the movie they are similar to, so movies similar to ones i liked count more than movies similar to ones i hated:

msg.data:
Now, let’s go through each movie i rated one at a time, and build up a list of possible recommendations based on the movies similar to the ones i rated.

So for each movie i rated, I’ll receive the list of similar movies from our correlation matrix. I’ll then scale those correlation scores by how well i rated the movie they are similar to, so movies similar to ones i liked count more than movies similar to ones i hated:

paragraphs.text:
%python

simCandidates = pd.Series()
for i in range(0, len(myRatings.index)):
    print "Adding sims for " + myRatings.index[i] + "..."
    # Retrieve similar movies to this one that i rated
    sims = corrMatrix[myRatings.index[i]].dropna()
    # Now scale its similarity by how well i rated this movie
    sims = sims.map(lambda x: x * myRatings[i])
    # Add the score to the list of similarity candidates
    simCandidates = simCandidates.append(sims)

# Clance at our results so far:
print "sorting..."
simCandidates.sort_values(inplace = True, ascending = False)
print simCandidates.head(10)
